ule id=\"R###\" importance=\"critical\" check=\"each message\">\n[Specific rule to prevent this issue]\n</rule>\n```\n\n#### User Prompt Improvements\nShow before/after with specific language:\n```\n❌ AVOID: \"Write tests for the commands\"\n✅ BETTER: \"Update tests/test_commands.py to add test cases for StatusCommand\"\n\n❌ AVOID: \"Make it better\"\n✅ BETTER: \"Refactor to reduce complexity while maintaining existing behavior\"\n```\n\n#### Subagent Configuration\nIf using subagents, suggest improvements:\n```markdown\n---\nname: [agent-name]\ndescription: Use PROACTIVELY to [specific trigger]. MUST [key requirement]\ntools: [specific tools only]\n---\n\n[Focused system prompt]\n```\n\n#### Hook Configuration\nIf applicable, suggest hooks to catch issues:\n```json\n{\n  \"hooks\": {\n    \"PreToolUse\": [{\n      \"matcher\": \"Write\",\n      \"hooks\": [{\n        \"type\": \"command\",\n        \"command\": \"[validation script]\"\n      }]\n    }]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n### 4. Implementation Checklist\n\nProvide actionable steps:\n- [ ] Add rule to ~/.claude/CLAUDE.md or project CLAUDE.md\n- [ ] Update agent configuration if using subagents\n- [ ] Test with improved prompt on same task\n- [ ] Configure hooks if pattern repeats\n- [ ] Document in project conventions\n\n## Output Structure\n\n### 🔍 What Went Wrong\n[Specific behavior that was problematic]\n\n### 🎯 Why It Happened\n**Primary Cause**: [Most likely reason]\n**Contributing Factors**: [Other issues that made it worse]\n\n### 🛠️ How to Fix It\n\n#### Add to CLAUDE.md\n```xml\n<rule id=\"R[next]\" importance=\"critical\">\n[Exact rule text to add]\n</rule>\n```\n\n#### Improve Your Prompts\n```\nWhen asking for [task type]:\n✅ \"[Specific improved prompt]\"\n\nKey phrases that help:\n- \"Update existing file at [path]\"\n- \"Following existing patterns in [file]\"\n- \"Without adding new dependencies\"\n```\n\n#### Configure Agent/Subagent (if applicable)\n```yaml\ndescription: [Improved description with triggers]\ntools: [Restricted tool list]\n```\n\n### 📚 Lessons Learned\n**Pattern**: [What to watch for]\n**Principle**: [Underlying concept]\n**Prevention**: [Proactive measure]\n\n### ✅ Verification Steps\n1. Test the same task with new configuration\n2. Check if agent follows the new rules\n3. Iterate if needed\n\n## Analysis Guidelines\n- Be specific - reference exact files and line numbers when possible\n- Focus on prevention - rules that stop issues before they occur\n- Test recommendations - ensure they're practical and effective\n- Reference Claude Code docs - link to relevant documentation sections"
